The General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) (Regulation (EU) 2016/679) is a regulation by which the European Parliament, the Council of the European Union and the European Commission intend to strengthen and unify data protection for all individuals within the European Union (EU). After four years of preparation and debate the GDPR was finally approved by the EU Parliament on 14 April 2016. Enforcement date: 25 May 2018 ‚Äì at which time those organizations in non-compliance may face heavy fines. More info at
GDPR Portal.
wpDiscuz has many tools and options to help you with GDPR compliance
Please read the following documentation, go through all settings and make sure your website comment section is correctly configured to comply the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR):
