Our privacy notice governs our privacy practices when you are using our websites, https://www.sitejabber.com, https://www.sitejabber.com/business, https://biz.sitejabber.com, our software as service called Jabio, our mobile app, and AI technology services, hereinafter and collectively referred to as the website.
Our privacy notice tells you what personal data and nonpersonal data we collect from you, how we collect them, how we protect them, how we disclose them, how you can access and change them, and how you can limit our disclosure of them. Our privacy notice also explains certain legal rights that you have concerning your personal data. Any capitalized terms not defined herein will have the same meaning as where they are defined elsewhere on our website.
Definitions
The terms ‚Äúus‚Äù, ‚Äúwe‚Äù, and ‚Äúour‚Äù refer to the owner of this Website.
‚ÄòNONPERSONAL DATA‚Äô (NPD) means any information that is in no way personally identifiable.
‚ÄòPERSONAL DATA‚Äô (PD) means any information relating to an identified or identifiable natural person (‚Äòdata subject‚Äô); an identifiable natural person can be identified directly or indirectly by reference to an identifier such as a name, an identification number, location data, an online identifier, or to one or more factors specific to the physical, physiological, genetic, mental, economic, cultural, or social identity of that natural person. PD is in many ways the same as Personally Identifiable Information (PII). However, PD is broader in scope and covers more data.
‚ÄòSENSITIVE PERSONAL DATA‚Äô (SPD) is a consumer‚Äôs social security, driver‚Äôs license, state identification card, or passport number; a consumer‚Äôs account log-in, financial account, debit card, or credit card number in combination with any required security, access code, password, or credentials allowing access to an account; a consumer‚Äôs exact geolocation; a consumer‚Äôs ethnic or racial origin, religious or philosophical beliefs, or union membership; the contents of a consumer‚Äôs mail, text messages, and email unless the business is the intended receiver of the communication; a consumer‚Äôs genetic data; the processing of biometric data to uniquely identify a consumer; personal information collected and analyzed about a consumer‚Äôs health; sex life or sexual orientation. Sensitive personal information that is "publicly available" is considered sensitive personal information or personal information.
Our Compliance with the Data Privacy Network
GGL Projects, Inc. complies with the EU-U.S. Data Privacy Framework (EU-U.S. DPF) and the UK Extension to the EU-U.S. DPF, and the Swiss-U.S. Data Privacy Framework (Swiss-U.S. DPF) as set forth by the U.S. Department of Commerce about the collection, processing, retention, and protection of customer personal data transferred from the European Union, United Kingdom, and/or Switzerland to the United States. Consistent with our commitment to protect customer personal data about individuals in these geographical areas, GGL Projects, Inc. has certified to the Department of Commerce that it adheres to the Data Privacy Framework of Notice, Choice, and Accountability for Onward Transfer, Security, Data Integrity and Purpose of Limitation, Access, Recourse, Enforcement and Liability. If there is any conflict between the terms in this privacy policy and the EU-U.S. DPF Principles and/or the Swiss-U.S. DPF Principles, the Principles shall govern. More information on GGL Projects, Inc.‚Äôs participation in the EU-U.S. and Swiss-U.S. and United Kingdom Data Privacy Framework is available at https://www.dataprivacyframework.gov/
Accountability for Onward Transfer
GGL Projects, Inc. is accountable for customer personal data that we receive and subsequently transfer to third parties. If third parties that process customer personal data on our behalf do so in a manner that does not comply with the Data Privacy Framework, we are accountable, unless we prove that we are not responsible for the event giving rise to the damage.
Contact information and customer personal data are accessible only by those GGL Projects, Inc. employees and consultants who have a reasonable need to access such information for us to fulfill contractual, legal and professional obligations. All of our employees and consultants have entered into confidentiality agreements.
Enforcement and Liability
GGL Projects, Inc. is subject to the jurisdiction and enforcement and investigatory authority of the United States Federal Trade Commission. GGL Projects, Inc. also commits to periodically reviewing and verifying the accuracy of this privacy notice and the company‚Äôs compliance with the principles, and remedying issues identified. All employees of GGL Projects, Inc. that have access to personally identifiable information covered by this privacy notice in the U.S. are responsible for conducting themselves in accordance with it. The failure of a GGL Projects, Inc. employee to comply with this privacy notice may result in disciplinary action up to and including termination.
Self-assessment Approach
GGL Projects, Inc. complies with the Data Privacy Framework by utilizing the self-assessment approach as specified by the U.S. Department of Commerce. The assessment is conducted on an annual basis to ensure that all of GGL Projects, Inc.‚Äôs relevant privacy practices are being followed in conformance with this Data Privacy Framework. Any employee that GGL Projects, Inc. determines violates these policies will be subject to discipline, up to and including termination of employment and/or criminal prosecution.
Dispute Resolution
GGL Projects, Inc. agrees with the EU-U.S., Swiss and United Kingdom Data Privacy Framework by fully investigating and attempting to resolve any complaint or dispute regarding the use and disclosure of customer personal data in violation of this privacy notice. Any questions or concerns regarding the use or disclosure of personal data should first be directed to the owner of this website; or if the question or concern is from our customer, then to GGL Projects, Inc. at the address given at the top of this privacy notice.
[When valid, we will comply with the Data Privacy Network dispute resolution requirements. Otherwise, our choice of law, jurisdiction, and arbitration provisions included in our terms and conditions will apply.]
In compliance with the EU-U.S. DPF and the UK Extension to the EU-U.S. DPF and the Swiss-U.S. DPF, GGL Projects, Inc. commits to refer unresolved complaints concerning our handling of personal data received in reliance on the EU-U.S. DPF and the UK Extension to the EU-U.S. DPF and the Swiss-U.S. DPF to ICDR-AAA DPF IRM Service, an alternative dispute resolution provider based in the United States. If you do not receive timely acknowledgment of your DPF Principles-related complaint from us, or if we have not addressed your DPF Principles-related complaint to your satisfaction, please visit https://go.adr.org/dpf_irm.html for more information or to file a complaint. The services of ICDR-AAA DPF IRM Service are provided at no cost to you.
Under certain conditions, you may invoke binding arbitration for complaints regarding DPF compliance not resolved by any of the other DPF mechanisms. For additional information please visit
https://www.dataprivacyframework.gov/framework-article/ANNEX-I-introduction
.
GGL Projects, Inc. will cooperate with the United States Federal Trade Commissions and any data protection authorities in the investigation and resolution of complaints that cannot be resolved between GGL Projects, Inc. and the complainant that are brought to a relevant data protection authority.
